OL,3,CInside Makerfield: How Burnham defied
OL,4,Cthe polls in historic by-election
OL,6,FReform candidate Rob Kenyon won 34.5%
OL,7,Fof the vote, while Restore Britain's
OL,8,FRebecca Shepherd won 6.8%, which
OL,9,Ftogether come to 41.3%.
OL,11,FMr Burnham's vote share was also
OL,12,Fhigher than the figure achieved by his
OL,13,Fpredecessor Josh Simons at the 2024
OL,14,Fgeneral election, which was 45.2%, and
OL,15,Franks as Labour's best performance in
OL,16,Fthe seat since 2017.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
