OL,3,CInside Makerfield: How Burnham defied
OL,4,Cthe polls in historic by-election
OL,6,FThis is the Tories' second lowest
OL,7,Fshare of the vote at a Westminster by-
OL,8,Felection since the Second World War.
OL,10,FThe lowest occurred a few months ago
OL,11,Fat the Gorton and Denton by-election
OL,12,Fin February, when the Tories won only
OL,13,F1.9% of the vote.
OL,15,FGreen party candidate Sarah Wakefield
OL,16,Ffinished fifth with 0.7%, while
OL,17,FLiberal Democrat candidate Jake Austin
OL,18,Fcame sixth with 0.4% ` the lowest for
OL,19,Fthe Lib Dems at any by-election since
OL,20,Fthe party was founded in 1988.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
