OL,3,CInside Makerfield: How Burnham defied
OL,4,Cthe polls in historic by-election
OL,6,FThere was a swing in the share of the
OL,7,Fvote from Reform to Labour of 3.4
OL,8,Fpercentage points ` the equivalent of
OL,9,Fmore than three in 100 people who
OL,10,Fvoted Reform at the 2024 general
OL,11,Felection switching to Labour this time.
OL,13,FMr Burnham's majority over Mr Kenyon
OL,14,Fwas 9,231, nearly 4,000 more than Josh
OL,15,FSimons' majority in 2024 over Mr
OL,16,FKenyon of 5,399.
OL,18,FMr Burnham also pushed up the size of
OL,19,FLabour's lead over Reform from 13
OL,20,Fpercentage points in 2024 to 20 points.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
