OL,3,CInside Makerfield: How Burnham defied
OL,4,Cthe polls in historic by-election
OL,6,FThe turnout in Makerfield was 58.7%,
OL,7,Fthe highest for a parliamentary by-
OL,8,Felection in nearly seven years.
OL,10,FThe last time a by-election had a
OL,11,Fhigher turnout was the contest in
OL,12,FBrecon and Radnorshire in August 2019,
OL,13,Fwhich saw the Liberal Democrats win
OL,14,Fthe seat from the Conservatives, when
OL,15,Fturnout was 59.6%.
OL,17,FThe jump in turnout meant more votes
OL,18,Fwere up for grabs, with Mr Burnham
OL,19,Fwinning a total of 24,927, an increase
OL,20,Fon the 18,202 won by Mr Simons in 2024.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
